            <p> After finishing my Traineestage, I decided to continued working in the Team DSC, where i currently work.
            </p>
            <p><a href="https://www.siga.swiss/ch_de" target="_blank">SIGA</a> is a medium sized international Company,
                that sells "building envelop sealing" I.e. the tape and membranes used to keep the heat (or cold) inside
                your house. Those sealings are produced in Swiss and thus we need to produce them as efficiently as
                possible, in order to stay relevant against other suppliers.

                In order to achieve that, SIGA adapted the <a
                    href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toyota_Production_System" target="_blank">Toyota Production
                    System</a>Philosophy.
                In practice this means that each day everyone writes down ideas how we could improve the processes. And
                then (after working for 9 days normally) we have a day, where we make this ideas a reality. Even so this
                originated in a production environment, it is also followed in all other departments.
                I personally used this as a way to make the Process in the teams i was more reliable. Some of the most
                important things i pushed over this, was the introduction of a Test environment, GIT based version
                control as well as
                Pullrequest for Releases. Currently we work on the meaning of CleanCode in our Team, and how to enforce
                that.

            </p>

            <div class="container_with_background">
