                    <h2> Second Stage - Digital Supply Chain</h2>
                    <p> My second and also longest stage, was in the Digital Supply Chain (DSC). The goal of this Team
                        is to support the production teams as well as some teams closely related to the production (like Material Management, Quality Control, Maintenance). In addition to this
                        we are also the link between those departments and the rest of the digitalization departments, both in a technical as well as personal regard.
                    </p>
                    <p> The Team works in two week long Sprints following the Scrum setup, in order to be able to react to new requirements fast.
                        We also prioritize a close relationship to production very high, this means that every developer worked for two weeks in production, so that we know the Processes.
                        Furthermore when we release new functionality we make sure that we are also at the working location, so that we can react fast to problems, and the users can ask questions directly.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        We maintain (and develop) a multitude of different applications, some of the most important, are listed below. I personally worked on each of them, introducing new 
                        functionality to them, as well as debugging and proposing technical improvements. 
                        <ul><li>
                            Collection and visualization of Production Data.
                            <p> We connect each machine to Azure in order to collect different datapoint. This data is not only used for some of our other application, but also made accessible to 
                                Maintenance (and similar departments) in order to give them a Datadriven ground for analysis.
                                In addition we commonly made small evaluations to tackle urgent problems.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Overall equipment Efficiency
                            <p>Using the data gather above we also calculate the quality and efficiency of the machine. I.e. we calculate Scrap , down time due to maintenance as well as errors and how much the Machines produced</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Reporting to SAP
                            <p>The calculations above are also sent to SAP to manage Stock as well as additional information of those products (such as production speed.)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Traceability
                            <p> In order to know which part was produced out of what other part, we maintain a system of Powerapps to gather this data and make that data accessible for our Stakeholders.
                                While doing thi, we make sure that we impact the production as little as possible.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Pull System
                            <p> In order to enhance communication in the production, we provide a solution for sending simple signals form one machine to another.
                                <br> This solution was original based on a network of Raspberry pis, but we later moved that to a Powerapps solution,in order to increase stability. (And because the Devices approached end of live.)
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    </p>
                    <p> 
                        In this team i learned SQL and did most of my work with it. But i also managed devices (mostly Linux based) and a multitude of AZURE components. (Azure data Factory, Azure Logic Apps, Azure data Cluster, PowerBi, Powerapps, Powerautomate,...)
                        Another important part was providing first, second and third level support in a timely manner.
